76561198111460867,Not Recommended,601980,33789232,Posted: 25 July,all,risky.ashtreehouse,"Full disclosure - I paid all of £0.47  for this game.  Having played it, I think it's over-priced.  Even as a pre-release version, there are just so many things wrong with it that it's hard to even know where to start...I'll start with the seriously annoying VR style interface.  This is a game that clearly was either originally intended for VR headsets, or that they're hoping to turn into a VR game at some stage.  At present, it's a pain.The game itself bears absolutely no relation to the apparent game footage in the promo movie above.  Basically, it's like one of those annoying little mini-games you get in some real games - you know, you're falling out of plane, and you're having to avoid bits of falling debris or rising flak.In this case, you're swimming, trying to avoid objects like bizarrly shaped lumps of metal etc.  When you hit one, you bleed a bit.  Do it a couple of times, and the sharks come and eat you.And that's basically it.  Move left, right, up, down, avoiding objects until you hit a couple and die.  Hugely disappointing, compared to what it might have been."
